Holly Willoughby is yet to reveal her secret behind her incredible weight loss, but there are some known details. The This Morning presenter has slimmed down in recent years. Speaking to Prima magazine in 2017, she said: "I actually avoid talking about my diet and exercise regime. "I have interviewed so many people affected by eating disorders and I know that some people in chat rooms can really fixate on other people's diets. "I just can't contribute to that," she shrugged. READ MORE: Sheridan Smith weight loss: Behind TV star's impressive 2 stone drop "As long as I'm healthy, that's good enough for me. "I'm quite active and I try not to let the way I look be the main focus because it's not the most important thing." She echoed her statements when she told the Sunday Times in 2019 that she "deliberately" didn’t talk about it on TV or elsewhere. Holly said: "I don’t think it’s helpful to the conversation, for women generally. DON'T MISS...Fitness: Experts unveil exercise tip to 'extend your life expectancy' [LATEST]Dwayne Johnson abs: Diet plan for weight loss [DIET PLAN]Weight loss: Slimmer ditched 3 foods to combat her menopause [REAL LIFE] "As long as you are healthy and happy, that’s really all that matters." The presenter added: "It’s a personal thing for me. "I think that people get obsessive with it. "Everybody knows what leads to a healthy lifestyle, but it’s not up to me to give you a blow-by-blow account of what I’ve eaten that day. "It’s not helpful, and it’s not what’s important." That said, it is believed Holly loves Pilates and was recently spotted doing a bit of upside down yoga. The star was doing the Inverted Butterfly position, said to boost circulation, promote healing and help detoxify tissue.